                  <h2 align="center"><font size="4" face="Times New Roman, Times, serif"><strong>Medical Instructions</strong> </font></h2>
                  <p align="justify"><font size="3" face="Times New Roman, Times, serif">All United Nations appointments are
                      subject to receiving asatisfactory medical clearance by a
                      medical physician accredited to the UN. Our records show
                      the location(s)
                  for this purpose closest to your address as:</font></p>
                  <p align="justify"><font size="3" face="Times New Roman, Times, serif"> Any licensed practicing Medical Doctor.</font></p>
                  <p align="justify"><font size="3" face="Times New Roman, Times, serif">If you
                      have not already done so, please arrange to be examined by
                      a physician named above. This must be done as soon as possible,
                      as we cannot complete your appointment and arrange for your
                      travel until we have received a satisfactory report from
                      our Medical Director. <strong>If the physician named is not available,
                      or if no one has been designated, <u>please go to the nearest
                  well-established local hospital with X-ray facilities.</u></strong> </font></p>
                  <p align="justify"><font size="3" face="Times New Roman, Times, serif">Examining
                      physicians should use the enclosed Entry Medical Examination
                      form, MS.2 (11-01)(4 pages); the first two pages to be filled
                      out and signed by you and the third and fourth to be filled
                  out and signed by your physician. </font></p>
                  <p align="justify"><font size="3" face="Times New Roman, Times, serif"><strong>The physician should fax
                      to # 1 212 963 0193</strong> (or an alternative fax number may be
                      provided
                  as necessary) the following: </font></p>
                  <p><font size="3" face="Times New Roman, Times, serif">1. the complete MS.2 form (4
                  pages);</font></p>
                  <p><font size="3" face="Times New Roman, Times, serif"> 2. X-ray report (X-ray film not necessary); </font></p>
                  <p><font size="3" face="Times New Roman, Times, serif">3. lab
                      test results;
                  and</font></p>
                  <p><font size="3" face="Times New Roman, Times, serif"> 4. electrocardiogram (EKG) tracing, regardless of age.                  </font></p>
                  <p align="justify"><font size="3" face="Times New Roman, Times, serif"><strong>Please ensure that you have the immunizations and/or malaria
                  prophylaxis required prior to departure. </strong></font></p>
                  <p align="justify"><font size="3" face="Times New Roman, Times, serif">The United Nations
                      will reimburse you for the cost of this pre-placement medical
                      examination, consisting of those tests required to complete
                      the medical forms, the X-ray, and the electrocardiogram.
                      It is expected that the cost of pre-placement medical examinations
                      will be consistent with the prevailing medical fees of the
                      country concerned. The United Nations will not be responsible
                      for fees for medical procedures which are not required by
                      this
                      pre-placement examination and will not on any account be
                      responsible for
                      fees exceeding the equivalent of US$350. You are requested
                      to pay the examining physician, obtain a receipt of the bill
                and submit it for reimbursement when you report for duty.                  </font></p></td>
